# Session 2 - [1/22] - [Version Control and GitHub]

Version Control
- Version control keeps track of changes to files over time.
- Instead of saving many copies with different names (`essay_v1`, `essay_final`, etc.), version control = records and changes in an organized way. 
:contentReference[oaicite:0]{index=0}

Git
- Git: most widely used version control software.  
- Store your version control online so you are less likely to lose your work. 

  - GitHub
  - GitLab
  - BitBucket 

GitHub
- Tracks every change made 
- Backup code in the cloud.  
- Build a portfolio that employers can view 
- Collaborate easily with other people
- Host websites for free using GitHub Pages.  
